From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 15:16:52 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] video: rockchip: add DW-HDMI-QP bridge for RK3576

Fixed-mode (CEA VIC 16, 1080p60 RGB 8bpc) display bridge for the RK3576
DW HDMI QP controller, driving the Samsung HDPTX PHY.

Probe ungates the controller's internal CMU video and link QP clock
domains (CMU_CONFIG0 VIDQPCLK_OFF/LINKQPCLK_OFF) and sets
TIMER_BASE_CONFIG0 to the RK3576's 396 MHz reference. Registers inside
those QP domains (LINK_*, TMDS_FIFO_*, HDCP2LOGIC_*) raise synchronous
external aborts until the domains are ungated and the HDPTX PLL supplies
the link clock, so the ungate must precede any enable-path access.

The enable path brings the PHY PLL up on the pixel rate, selects TMDS
link mode and RGB 8bpc in the VO0 GRF, configures HDMI mode with
HDCP2_BYPASS and rekey keepout, emits the AVI InfoFrame, powers the
lanes on, opens the AVP video datapath (SWDISABLE), and clears AVMUTE
with a re-armed GCP. VIDEO_INTERFACE_CONFIG0 bit 21 is written last:
the field is HDMI_COLOR_DEPTH_OVR_VALUE and the value is a reserved
code Rockchip firmware uses as a bootloader-lit-the-display marker;
it is inert without the (undocumented) override enable. The bridge
claims the earc clock alongside the others its DT node names.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/video/rockchip/Kconfig               |  10 +
 drivers/video/rockchip/Makefile              |   1 +
 drivers/video/rockchip/dw_hdmi_qp_rockchip.c | 444 +++++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 455 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 drivers/video/rockchip/dw_hdmi_qp_rockchip.c

